.ds n) explain_iconv_close_or_die
.TH explain_iconv_close_or_die 3
.SH NAME
explain_iconv_close_or_die \- deallocate conversion descriptor and report errors
.if require_index \{
.XX "explain_iconv_close_or_die(3)" \
    "deallocate descriptor for character set conversion and report errors"
.\}
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <libexplain/iconv_close.h>
.sp 0.3
void explain_iconv_close_or_die(iconv_t cd);
.br
int explain_iconv_close_on_error(iconv_t cd);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]explain_iconv_close_or_die\fP function is used to call the
\f[I]iconv_close\fP(3) system call. On failure an explanation will be
printed to \f[I]stderr\fP, obtained from the \f[I]explain_iconv_close\fP(3)
function, and then the process terminates by calling
\f[CW]exit(EXIT_FAILURE)\fP.
.PP
The \f[B]explain_iconv_close_on_error\fP function is used to call the
\f[I]iconv_close\fP(3) system call. On failure an explanation will be
printed to \f[I]stderr\fP, obtained from the \f[I]explain_iconv_close\fP(3)
function, but still returns to the caller.
.TP 8n
\f[I]cd\fP
The cd, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]iconv_close\fP(3) system call.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SH RETURN VALUE
The \f[B]explain_iconv_close_or_die\fP function only returns on success,
see \f[I]iconv_close\fP(3) for more information. On failure, prints an
explanation and exits, it does not return.
.PP
The \f[B]explain_iconv_close_on_error\fP function always returns the value
return by the wrapped \f[I]iconv_close\fP(3) system call.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SH EXAMPLE
The \f[B]explain_iconv_close_or_die\fP function is intended to be used in a
fashion similar to the following example:
.RS
.ft CW
.nf
explain_iconv_close_or_die(cd);
.fi
.ft R
.RE
